    <name>
				<text>2.4.2.4 Limits of piecewise function</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Draw a graph of the following function for yourself:</p>
<p><span class="math inline">\(\qquad f(x)= 
\left\{
\begin{array}{ll} {@aa@} &amp; x&lt;{@ll@}\\
{@bb@} &amp; x= {@ll@} \\
{@cc@} &amp; x&gt; {@ll@}
\end{array} \right.\)</span></p>

<p>Find the following limits (if a limit does not exist type in <code>none</code>).</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}f(x) = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^-}f(x) = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow 0}f(x) = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p></li>
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow {@ll@}^+}f(x) = \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</p></li>
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow {@ll@}^-}f(x) = \) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]</p></li>
  <li><p>\(\lim_{x\rightarrow {@ll@}}f(x) = \) [[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]] [[feedback:prt6]]</p></li></ol>
<p><br></p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
